2.speaker: PENGUIN
2.character: どうしたの？　元気ないね

3.speaker: POLAR BEAR
3.character: パンダくん　いつもの？
3.definition: Do you want your usual, Panda?

4.speaker: PANDA
4.definition: Yes... Oh, but just a normal serving.

5.speaker: SASAKO
5.character: えっ！？　大盛りじゃないの？
5.definition: What? You don't want the larger serving?

6.speaker: PANDA
6.character: 今日から　ダイエットするの

8.speaker: PENGUIN
8.character: それは　インターネット

9.speaker: PENGUIN
9.character: それは　イヌイット

10.speaker: PENGUIN
10.character: それは　カルテット

12.speaker: PANDA
12.character: 実は　今日　動物園でさ…
12.definition: Well you see, at the zoo today...

14.speaker: PANDA
14.character: サービス　サービス
14.definition: Service, service. I'm glad you weren't hurt.

15.speaker: PENGUIN
15.character: それで　ダイエット？
15.definition: So you're starting a diet because of that?

16.speaker: PANDA
16.definition: Well, I always wished I was born a bit more slim. You care about your figure?

18.character: 生まれたときから おっさん体型なんだもん
18.definition: the physique of an old man since I was born.

19.speaker: PENGUIN
19.definition: Well, what do you want to look like?

21.speaker: PANDA
21.character: もっと　脚が長くて
21.definition: For my legs to be longer,

23.speaker: PANDA
23.definition: and for my face to be shaped like an inverted triangle, too.

24.speaker: CREEPY PANDA
24.character: ドリームパンダ　ハハハハハ！

25.speaker: PENGUIN
25.character: それ　かっこいいの？

26.speaker: POLAR BEAR
26.character: パンダくん 悪いヤツみたいになっちゃうね
26.definition: You'd look like a bad guy, Panda.

27.speaker: PANDA
27.character: いいの 僕　ワルに憧れてるから
27.definition: That's fine. I think bad guys are awesome.

30.speaker: PANDA
30.character: やっぱり　いつもので
30.definition: Could I get my usual after all?

31.speaker: SASAKO
31.definition: One large serving coming right up.

35.speaker: HANDA
35.character: パンダくん　起きなさい！

36.speaker: HANDA
36.character: たった　週２回のバイトなのに
36.definition: You only have to work twice a week,

37.character: 朝から居眠りしないでよ
37.definition: so could you not sleep as soon as you get here?

38.speaker: HANDA
38.character: はい　パンダだんご

39.speaker: PANDA
39.definition: I don't want them. What? Why?

40.speaker: PANDA
40.character: 今日から　ダイエットするの
40.definition: I'm starting my diet today. Diet?

41.speaker: FT PANDA
41.character: へぇ…　私なんか すっかり　メタボだけど
41.definition: Wow, I'm definitely overweight, but I'm not doing a thing.

42.speaker: PANDA
42.character: 昨日は　すべり台を 壊しちゃったしさ…
42.definition: Well, I broke the slide yesterday.

44.speaker: HANDA
44.character: あれは　柱が シロアリに食われてたからで
44.definition: The supports were eaten away by termites,

45.character: パンダくんのせいじゃないから

46.speaker: PANDA
46.character: それに　まだ若いのに おっさん体型だし…
46.definition: Not to mention, I'm young and have the physique of an old man.

47.speaker: HANDA
47.character: でも　それが自然なパンダだし
47.definition: Well, that's natural for a panda.

48.speaker: HANDA
48.character: そもそも パンダの名前の由来を知らないの？
48.definition: Don't you know where the name "panda" comes from?

49.speaker: PANDA
49.character: えっ　何？　かわいいとか？
49.definition: Ooh, what is it? Does it come from "cute"?

50.speaker: HANDA
50.character: まぁ　いろんな説があるんだけどさ そのうちの一つは…
50.definition: Well, there are multiple explanations. One of them goes like this... Long, long ago, there were foreigners exploring China.

51.speaker: HANDA
51.character: こうして　中国語の 「太った」という意味のパンダが
51.definition: So that's the explanation of the Chinese phrase for

52.character: 名前として 広まったという説があるんだ
52.definition: "the fat one" becoming the name for panda.

54.speaker: PANDA
54.character: なんか　すごくへこんできた…
54.definition: I'm starting to get really depressed.

55.speaker: FT PANDA
55.character: 世の中には　知らないほうが 幸せなこともあるよね
55.definition: There are many things in the world that you're better off not knowing. It's because of my job!

56.speaker: PANDA
56.definition: I got fat because all I do at work is sit around being bored, eat snacks, and nap!

57.speaker: HANDA
57.character: ヒマじゃないでしょう！

58.character: ちゃんと お客さんにサービスしなさい！
58.definition: You need to give the crowd more service!

59.speaker: PANDA
59.character: なんか最近　マンネリでさ…
59.definition: I'm stuck in a rut lately.

60.speaker: PANDA
60.character: タイヤやすべり台で遊ぶのも 飽きちゃって…
60.definition: I'm sick of playing on the tire swing and sliding down the slide.

62.speaker: PANDA
62.character: ねぇ　フィットネスゲーム持ってきていい？
62.definition: Hey, can I bring a fitness game?

64.speaker: FT PANDA
64.character: ゲルマニウム温浴　作ってよ
64.definition: Could you make a Germanium hot bath? Absolutely not.

65.speaker: PANDA
65.character: エアロビのお姉さんを呼ぼうよ
65.definition: Let's get an aerobics trainer lady.

66.speaker: HANDA
66.definition: I said no! If I only had some kind of motive.

67.speaker: PANDA
67.character: もっと　ダイエットやる気になるのにな
67.definition: Then I would feel more like dieting.

68.speaker: HANDA
68.character: まぁ　ダイエットしたいなら しっかりとサービスに励みなさい
68.definition: Well, if you want to go on a diet, you can start by actually providing service to the crowd.

70.speaker: PANDA
70.character: 僕って　やればできる子だから
70.definition: I can do it when it matters! Well then, do it, please.

71.speaker: KIDS
71.character: パンダさん　起きて～！

72.speaker: GIRLS
72.character: パンダさん　かわいい！

73.speaker: PANDA
73.character: サービス　サービス！

74.speaker: PANDA
74.character: サービス　サービス！

75.speaker: HANDA
75.character: かわいいって言われたときだけ 反応するね
75.definition: He only reacts when someone calls him cute. {\a6}Service, service!

76.speaker: GIRL
76.character: この下膨れ体型が かわいいんだよね
76.definition: His plump body is beyond cute!

77.speaker: GIRL
77.character: メタボパンダさんだね

78.speaker: PANDA
78.character: 目指せ　ドリームパンダ！

79.speaker: PANDA
79.character: パパンダー　パパンパン　パパンダー

80.speaker: PANDA
80.character: パパンダー　パンパンパン　パパンダー

85.speaker: KIDS
85.character: ダイエット　ダイエット！

86.speaker: PANDA
86.character: ダイエット　ダイエット！
86.definition: Diet, diet! Diet, diet! Diet, diet!

87.speaker: PANDA
87.character: 何だか　ドキドキするね

89.speaker: HANDA
89.character: ここんとこ ずっと頑張ってたんだから
89.definition: You've been working really hard lately.

90.speaker: PANDA
90.character: 目標　とりあえず　１３０キロ
90.definition: My goal, for now, is 130 kilograms.

93.speaker: HANDA
93.character: おめでとう　ダイエット成功だね

94.speaker: PANDA
94.character: 僕　もっと頑張って スリムなドリームパンダになるよ
94.definition: I'm going to work even harder to become a trim Dream Panda. Um, you don't have to work quite that hard.

95.speaker: HANDA
95.character: 頑張ったパンダくんに ご褒美があるよ
95.definition: I have a present for you since you worked so hard, Panda.

97.speaker: HANDA
97.character: 楽しく滑れるように 工夫してみたんだ
97.definition: I changed it up a little so it'll be more fun to slide on.

98.speaker: HANDA
98.character: パンダくんが マンネリって言ってたからね
98.definition: After all, you said you were in a rut.

99.speaker: PANDA
99.character: 半田さん　ありがとう

100.speaker: FT PANDA
100.character: 待ってたよ　一緒に初滑りしよう
100.definition: I was waiting for you. Let's go down for the first time together.

104.speaker: FT PANDA
104.character: あ　いや… お腹がつっかえて…(´･ω･)
104.definition: Um, well... Looks like my tummy got stuck.

105.speaker: PANDA
105.character: 常勤パンダさん　メタボ

106.speaker: HANDA
106.character: ハァー　作り直しかな…
106.definition: I guess I'll have to rebuild it.

109.speaker: PENGUIN
109.character: 何してるの　パンダくん
109.definition: Exactly what are you doing, Panda?

110.speaker: PENGUIN
110.character: どうしたの　その格好

111.speaker: PANDA
111.character: 悪いヤツな気分になってみたくて
111.definition: I wanted to feel like a bad guy.

112.speaker: PANDA
112.character: ワルな人って憧れちゃうな
112.definition: It's so cool to be bad!

113.speaker: SASAKO
113.character: パンダくん　いつもの？
113.definition: Would you like your usual, Panda?

114.speaker: PANDA
114.character: うん　あ　いや　ストロングコーヒー
114.definition: Yes! Wait, actually, could I get a strong coffee?

115.speaker: SASAKO
115.character: えっ　ストロング？　結構　苦いよ
115.definition: What? Strong? It's really bitter, though...

116.speaker: PANDA
116.character: 今日は　ワルの気分だから

120.speaker: SASAKO
120.character: ねぇ　ワルのどこに憧れたの？
120.definition: So, what made you think bad guys were so cool?

121.speaker: PANDA
121.character: ほら　僕って優柔不断だから
121.definition: Well, I have trouble making up my mind,

122.character: 強気な人が羨ましくって
122.definition: So I envy really decisive people.

123.speaker: PENGUIN
123.character: それ　ワルとは関係ないでしょ
123.definition: I don't think that has anything to do with being a bad guy.

125.speaker: PANDA
125.character: 僕に足りないのは ワイルドさだと思うんだ
125.definition: I think I lack a bit of a wild side.

128.speaker: POLAR BEAR
128.character: マイルドなコーヒーね
128.definition: I'll get you a lighter coffee.

129.speaker: PANDA
129.character: いろいろビデオを見て ワイルドなイメージを膨らませてみたの
129.definition: I watched a lot of videos to see what being wild is like.

131.speaker: PANDA
131.definition: Let's see... I present to you "candy" the color of bright, golden yellow.

132.speaker: PANDA
132.character: 越後屋　お主もワルよのう
132.definition: Well, aren't you a villain, Echigoya?

134.speaker: PENGUIN
134.character: 微妙に　ズレてない？　それ
134.definition: I think all of those are a little off somehow...

135.speaker: PANDA
135.character: イマイチ強気で ワイルドなイメージがつかめなくて
135.definition: I still can't get the image of strong and wild just yet. Strong and wild, huh?

136.speaker: POLAR BEAR
136.character: グリズリーくんとか　そうかも

138.speaker: POLAR BEAR
138.character: お店やってるから 夜　行ってみる？
138.definition: He runs a business. Do you want to go there tonight?

139.speaker: PANDA
139.character: グリズリーさんのお店って　この辺りなの？
139.definition: Is Mr. Grizzly's place somewhere around here?

141.speaker: POLAR BEAR
141.character: ここを抜けると　すぐそこ
141.definition: You'll see it right after we exit this tunnel.

143.speaker: POLAR BEAR
143.character: パンダくん　こっち　こっち

144.speaker: PANDA
144.character: 確かに　ワイルドなお店だね

146.speaker: POLAR BEAR
146.character: こんばんは　グリズリーくん

147.speaker: GRIZZLY
147.character: よお　シロクマ 久しぶりじゃねえか
147.definition: Hey, Polar Bear. It's been a while.

148.speaker: PANDA
148.character: 本当に　ワイルドだ…

149.speaker: GRIZZLY
149.character: 相変わらず なまっちろい野郎だぜ　この　シロクマ野郎
149.definition: As white as ever, you damn polar bear.

150.speaker: GRIZZLY
150.character: ちょっと焼いてこいよ　日サロで
150.definition: Go get a tan at the tanning salon.

151.speaker: POLAR BEAR
151.character: いや…　行っても たぶん変わらない
151.definition: No... I don't think that would make a difference. I brought a friend with me today.

153.speaker: GRIZZLY
153.character: 白いのか　黒いのか はっきりしねえ野郎だな
153.definition: Can't make up your damn mind whether you're black or white?

155.speaker: GRIZZLY
155.character: まあ　いいか　座れ

160.speaker: GRIZZLY
160.definition: For you? Um... a large serving of bamboo...

161.speaker: GRIZZLY
161.character: 悪いな　ヘルシーなものは 置いてないんだ
161.definition: Sorry, we don't have any of that healthy crap.

162.speaker: PANDA
162.character: じゃ…　じゃあ… アイスコーヒー　お願いします
162.definition: T-Then could I get an iced coffee?

163.speaker: GRIZZLY
163.character: ソフトドリンクもないね
163.definition: Don't have any soft drinks either.

164.speaker: PANDA
164.character: じゃあ　笹の入ったパフェを お願いします
164.definition: Then could I get a parfait with bamboo leaves... I just told you we don't have any of that healthy crap here!

166.speaker: GRIZZLY
166.definition: Looks like I don't have a choice.

167.speaker: GRIZZLY
167.character: シロクマの友人だ 特別に　コーヒー　いれてやるよ
167.definition: You're a friend of Polar Bear's. I'll get you some coffee.

170.speaker: PANDA
170.character: あっ　いや…　ありで

171.speaker: PANDA
171.character: あっ　やっぱ　なしで
171.definition: Actually, no thank— Black or not?!

172.speaker: POLAR BEAR
172.character: もう…　相変わらず短気だな

173.speaker: GRIZZLY
173.character: まあ　パンダが白黒はっきりしたら
173.definition: Well, if a panda could decide between black or white,

174.character: シロクマか ただのクマになっちまうよな
174.definition: a polar bear would be just a regular bear. Mr. Grizzly is really scary.

177.speaker: ALLIGATOR
177.character: アンタ　丸々と太ってて うまそうだな
177.definition: You're so plump and round, and you look delicious. I wonder how I should eat you.

178.speaker: ALLIGATOR
178.definition: Maybe I'll just swallow you whole {\i1}(marunomi){\i0}.

181.speaker: POLAR BEAR
181.definition: Perhaps miso cucumbers {\i1}(morokyuu){\i0}. {I think they're actually made with like miso or some kind of fermented soy sauce... I thought pickled sounded easier but maybe "cucumbers with miso"}{Z: Changed this a bit. If you don't like change feel free to change back.} Maybe I'll slice you up into sashimi {\i1}(ikezukuri){\i0}. {he means when you get sashimi and it's presented to you with the head and tail as decoration... I didn't know how else to word that without it being too wordy ^^;;}

184.speaker: GRIZZLY
184.character: あんまり他の客を 怖がらすんじゃねえよ
184.definition: Don't be scaring the other customers too much.

187.speaker: GRIZZLY
187.character: 悪かったな ほらよ　コーヒーだ
187.definition: Sorry about that.  Here you go, coffee.

188.speaker: PANDA
188.character: グリズリーさん　ありがとう！

189.speaker: PANDA
189.character: ねぇ　グリズリーさん

191.speaker: PANDA
191.character: あの写真って グリズリーさんだよね？
191.definition: That's you in that picture, right? Oh, that.

192.speaker: GRIZZLY
192.character: 愛車で　アメリカを 横断したときのやつさ
192.definition: That's when I drove across America on my baby.

194.speaker: GRIZZLY
194.character: よかったぜ　地平線まで続く道を ぶっ飛ばしてよ
194.definition: It was great. We rode onward toward the horizon. Wow, that's so cool!

195.speaker: GRIZZLY
195.character: どうせ　お前らはスローライフとかいって ダラダラ暮らしてやがんだろ？
195.definition: You guys probably enjoy having a slow life with no excitement.

198.speaker: GRIZZLY
198.character: 言い方変えただけだろ
198.definition: Doesn't matter what you call it.

199.speaker: POLAR BEAR
199.character: ゆっくりでも そんなに変わらないよ
199.definition: The slow life's not that different.

200.speaker: GRIZZLY
200.character: 昔からマイペースだよな　お前は
200.definition: You always did march to the beat of your own drum.

201.speaker: GRIZZLY
201.character: 人生は　一度きりだぜ

202.speaker: GRIZZLY
202.character: 熱く　ぶっ飛ばさなきゃな
202.definition: You have to go all out.

203.speaker: PANDA
203.character: グリズリーさん　すごくかっこいいね

204.character: 僕　そういうの大好き！
204.definition: I really admire that. Well, you seem to understand things even

205.character: 話のわかるヤツじゃないか
205.definition: though you're a friend of Polar Bear.

206.speaker: GRIZZLY
206.character: ほら　冷めちまうぞ　飲めよ
206.definition: Hurry up and drink it, it'll get cold.

207.speaker: GRIZZLY
207.character: どうだ？ アイリッシュコーヒーにしてみたんだ
207.definition: How is it? I made an Irish coffee.

208.speaker: GRIZZLY
208.character: まっ　コーヒーより　ウイスキーのほうが 多かったかもな
208.definition: Well, I may have put in more whiskey than coffee, though.

210.speaker: PANDA
210.character: バルルルル…　グフッ　フフフ
210.definition: Vroom, vroom... You should bring him again.

211.speaker: GRIZZLY
211.character: 今度は　インスタントじゃないコーヒーを いれてやるから
211.definition: I won't use instant coffee next time.

212.speaker: POLAR BEAR
212.character: うん　マイルドで　よろしくね
212.definition: Yeah, make it mild next time.

215.speaker: PANDA
215.character: シロクマくん　運んでくれたんだね
215.definition: You carried me out, Polar Bear?

219.speaker: PANDA
219.character: それと　もうひとつ　ありがとう

220.speaker: PANDA
220.character: 僕　だいぶ　ワイルドってのが わかった気がするよ
220.definition: I think I have a better idea of wild now.

221.speaker: POLAR BEAR
221.character: そう　それならよかった
221.definition: That's good. I'm glad I could help.

222.speaker: PANDA
222.character: シロクマくん　どう？　これ
222.definition: What do you think, Polar Bear? Is this wild?

223.speaker: POLAR BEAR
223.character: いやぁ　マイルドかな
223.definition: No, I think it's more mild.

225.speaker: POLAR BEAR
225.character: あれ？　パンダくん　どこ行くの？
225.definition: Oh? Where are you going, Panda?

226.speaker: PANDA
226.character: ワルは後ろを振り返らない

228.speaker: PANDA
228.character: ペンギンさん　ペンギンさん

229.speaker: PENGUIN
229.character: どうしたの　パンダ君
229.definition: What's wrong, Panda? Why doesn't anyone like you, Mr. Penguin? That's not true! I'm liked by everyone!

230.speaker: PANDA
230.character: どっちでもいいじゃない

231.speaker: POLAR BEAR
231.character: 次回のしろくまカフェは

232.speaker: POLAR BEAR
232.character: 鉛筆書きでお送りします
232.definition: will be presented done in pencil drawings.
